
@@libLamentations 
</br>1 :
</br>1 -
</br>22 
<p></p>
</br>1 O how she has come to sit solitary, the city that was abundant with people!
@@citzHow she has become like a widow, she that was populous among the nations!
@@citzHow she that was a princess among the jurisdictional districts has come to be for forced labor!
<p></p>
</br>2 Profusely she weeps during the night, and her tears are upon her cheeks.
@@citzShe has no one to comfort her from among all her lovers.
@@citzAll her very own companions have dealt treacherously with her. They have become enemies to her.
<p></p>
</br>3 Judah has gone into exile because of the affliction and because of the abundance of servitude.
@@citzShe herself has had to dwell among the nations. No resting-place has she found.
@@citzAll those who were persecuting her have overtaken her among distressing circumstances.
<p></p>
</br>4 The ways of Zion are mourning, because there are none coming to the festival.
@@citzAll her gates are laid desolate; her priests are sighing.
@@citzHer virgins are grief-stricken, and she herself has bitterness.
<p></p>
</br>5 Her adversaries have become the head. Those who are her enemies are unconcerned.
@@citzBecause Jehovah himself has brought grief to her on account of the abundance of her transgressions,
@@citzHer own children have walked captive before the adversary.
<p></p>
</br>6 And from the daughter of Zion there goes out all her splendor.
@@citzHer princes have proved to be like stags that have found no pasturage;
@@citzAnd they keep walking without power before the pursuer.
<p></p>
</br>7 Jerusalem has remembered [in] the days of her affliction and of her homeless people
@@citzAll her desirable things that happened to be from days of long ago.
@@citzWhen her people fell into the hand of the adversary and she had no helper,
@@citzThe adversaries saw her. They laughed over her collapse.
<p></p>
</br>8 Jerusalem has committed outright sin. That is why she has become a mere abhorrent thing.
@@citzAll who were honoring her have treated her as something cheap, for they have seen her nakedness.
@@citzShe herself is also sighing and turns her back.
<p></p>
</br>9 Her uncleanness is in her skirts. She did not remember the future for her,
@@citzAnd down she goes in a wondrous manner. No comforter does she have.
@@citzO Jehovah, see my affliction, for the enemy has put on great airs.
<p></p>
</br>10 The adversary has spread out his own hand against all her desirable things.
@@citzFor she has seen nations that have come into her sanctuary,
@@citzWhom you commanded that they should not come into the congregation belonging to you.
<p></p>
</br>11 All her people are sighing; they are looking for bread.
@@citzThey have given their desirable things for something to eat, in order to refresh the soul.
@@citzSee, O Jehovah, and do look, for I have become as a valueless woman.
<p></p>
</br>12 Is it nothing to all YOU who are passing along the way? Look and see.
@@citzDoes there exist any pain like my pain that has been severely dealt out to me,
@@citzWith which Jehovah has caused grief in the day of his burning anger?
<p></p>
</br>13 From the height he has sent fire into my bones, and he subdues each one.
@@citzHe has spread out a net for my feet. He has turned me backward.
@@citzHe has made me a woman laid desolate. All the day I am ill.
<p></p>
</br>14 He has kept himself alert against my transgressions. In his hand they intertwine one another.
@@citzThey have come up upon my neck. My power has stumbled.
@@citzJehovah has given me into the hand of those against whom I am unable to rise up.
<p></p>
</br>15 All my powerful ones Jehovah has tossed aside from the midst of me.
@@citzHe has called against me a meeting, in order to break my young men to pieces.
@@citzJehovah has trodden the very winepress belonging to the virgin daughter of Judah.
<p></p>
</br>16 Over these things I am weeping as a woman. My eye, my eye is running down with waters.
@@citzFor a comforter has become far away from me, someone to refresh my soul.
@@citzMy sons have become those laid desolate, for the enemy has put on great airs.
<p></p>
</br>17 Zion has spread out her hands. No comforter does she have.
@@citzJehovah has given a command concerning Jacob to all who are around him as his adversaries.
@@citzJerusalem has become an abhorrent thing in among them.
<p></p>
</br>18 Jehovah is righteous, for it is against his mouth that I have rebelled.
@@citzListen, now, all YOU peoples, and see my pain.
@@citzMy own virgins and my own young men have gone into captivity.
<p></p>
</br>19 I have called to those intensely loving me. They themselves have tricked me.
@@citzIn the city my own priests and my own old men have expired,
@@citzWhile they had to look for something to eat for themselves that they might refresh their soul.
<p></p>
</br>20 See, O Jehovah, for I am in sore straits. My very intestines are in a ferment.
@@citzMy heart has been overturned in the midst of me, for I have been absolutely rebellious.
@@citzOutside the sword caused bereavement of children. Within the house it is the same as death.
<p></p>
</br>21 People have heard how I myself am sighing as a woman. There is no comforter for me.
@@citzAll my enemies themselves have heard of my calamity. They have exulted, because you yourself have done [it].
@@citzYou will certainly bring the day that you have proclaimed, that they may become like me.
<p></p>
</br>22 May all their badness come before you, and deal severely with them,
@@citzJust as you have dealt severely with me on account of all my transgressions.
@@citzFor my sighs are many, and my heart is ill.
@@libLamentations 
</br>2 :
</br>1 -
</br>22 
<p></p>
</br>1 O how Jehovah in his anger beclouds the daughter of Zion!
@@citzHe has thrown down from heaven to earth the beauty of Israel.
@@citzAnd he has not remembered his footstool in the day of his anger.
<p></p>
</br>2 Jehovah has swallowed up, he has shown no compassion upon any abiding places of Jacob.
@@citzIn his fury he has torn down the fortified places of the daughter of Judah.
@@citzHe has brought into contact with the earth, he has profaned the kingdom and her princes.
<p></p>
</br>3 In the heat of anger he has cut down every horn of Israel.
@@citzHe has turned his right hand back from before the enemy;
@@citzAnd in Jacob he keeps burning like a flaming fire that has devoured all around.
<p></p>
</br>4 He has trodden his bow like an enemy. His right hand has taken its position
@@citzLike an adversary, and he kept killing all those desirable to the eyes.
@@citzInto the tent of the daughter of Zion he has poured out his rage, just like fire.
<p></p>
</br>5 Jehovah has become like an enemy. He has swallowed down Israel.
@@citzHe has swallowed down all her dwelling towers; he has brought his fortified places to ruin.
@@citzAnd in the daughter of Judah he makes mourning and lamentation abound.
<p></p>
</br>6 And he treats his booth violently like that in a garden. He has brought his festival to ruin.
@@citzJehovah has caused to be forgotten in Zion festival and sabbath,
@@citzAnd in his angry denunciation he shows no respect for king and priest.
<p></p>
</br>7 Jehovah has cast off his altar. He has spurned his sanctuary.
@@citzInto the hand of the enemy he has surrendered the walls of her dwelling towers.
@@citzIn the house of Jehovah they have let out [their] own voice, as in the day of a festival.
<p></p>
</br>8 Jehovah has thought of bringing the wall of the daughter of Zion to ruin.
@@citzHe has stretched out the measuring line. He has not turned back his hand from swallowing up.
@@citzAnd he causes rampart and wall to go mourning. Together they have faded away.
<p></p>
</br>9 Her gates have sunk down into the very earth. He has destroyed and broken her bars in pieces.
@@citzHer king and her princes are among the nations. There is no law.
@@citzHer own prophets also have found no vision from Jehovah.
<p></p>
</br>10 The older men of the daughter of Zion sit down on the earth, [where] they keep silence.
@@citzThey have brought up dust upon their head. They have girded on sackcloth.
@@citzThe virgins of Jerusalem have brought their head down to the very earth.
<p></p>
</br>11 My eyes have come to their end in sheer tears. My intestines are in a ferment.
@@citzMy liver has been poured out to the very earth, on account of the crash of the daughter of my people,
@@citzBecause of the fainting away of child and suckling in the public squares of the town.
<p></p>
</br>12 To their mothers they kept saying: “Where are grain and wine?”
@@citzBecause of their fainting away like someone slain in the public squares of the city,
@@citzBecause of their soul being poured out into the bosom of their mothers.
<p></p>
</br>13 Of what shall I use you as a witness? What shall I liken to you, O daughter of Jerusalem?
@@citzWhat shall I make equal to you, that I may comfort you, O virgin daughter of Zion?
@@citzFor your breakdown is just as great as the sea. Who can bring healing to you?
<p></p>
</br>14 Your own prophets have visioned for you worthless and unsatisfying things,
@@citzAnd they have not uncovered your error in order to turn back your captivity,
@@citzBut they kept visioning for you worthless and misleading pronouncements.
<p></p>
</br>15 At you all those passing along on the road have clapped their hands.
@@citzThey have whistled and kept wagging their head at the daughter of Jerusalem, [saying:]
@@citz“Is this the city of which they used to say, ‘It is the perfection of prettiness, an exultation for all the earth’?”
<p></p>
</br>16 At you all your enemies have opened their mouth.
@@citzThey have whistled and kept grinding the teeth. They have said: “We will swallow [her] down.
@@citzThis indeed is the day that we have hoped for. We have found! We have seen!”
<p></p>
</br>17 Jehovah has done what he had in mind. He has accomplished his saying,
@@citzWhat he had commanded from the days of long ago. He has torn down and shown no compassion.
@@citzAnd over you he causes the enemy to rejoice. He has made the horn of your adversaries high.
<p></p>
</br>18 Their heart has cried out to Jehovah, O wall of the daughter of Zion.
@@citzCause tears to descend just like a torrent day and night.
@@citzGive no numbness to yourself. May the pupil of your eye not keep quiet.
<p></p>
</br>19 Rise up! Whine during the night at the start of the morning watches.
@@citzPour out your heart before the face of Jehovah just like water.
@@citzRaise to him your palms on account of the soul of your children,
@@citzWho are fainting away because of famine at the head of all the streets.
<p></p>
</br>20 See, O Jehovah, and do look to the one to whom you have dealt severely in this manner.
@@citzShould the women keep eating their own fruitage, the children born fully formed,
@@citzOr in the sanctuary of Jehovah should priest and prophet be killed?
<p></p>
</br>21 Boy and old man have lain down on the earth of the streets.
@@citzMy virgins and my young men themselves have fallen by the sword.
@@citzYou have killed in the day of your anger. You have slaughtered; you have had no compassion.
<p></p>
</br>22 As in the day of a festival you proceeded to call out my places of alien residence all around.
@@citzAnd in the day of the wrath of Jehovah there proved to be no escapee or survivor;
@@citzThose whom I brought forth fully formed and reared, my enemy himself exterminated them.
@@libLamentations 
</br>3 :
</br>1 -
</br>66 
<p></p>
</br>1 I am the able-bodied man that has seen affliction because of the staff of his fury.
<p></p>
</br>2 It is I whom he has led and makes to walk in darkness and not in light.
<p></p>
</br>3 Indeed, it is against me that he repeatedly turns his hand all day long.
<p></p>
</br>4 He has caused my flesh and my skin to wear away. He has broken my bones.
<p></p>
</br>5 He has built against me, that he may encircle [me] with poisonous plant and hardship.
<p></p>
</br>6 In dark places he has made me sit like men dead for a long time.
<p></p>
</br>7 He has blocked me up as with a stone wall, that I may not go forth. He has made my copper fetters heavy.
<p></p>
</br>8 Also, when I call for aid and cry for help, he actually hampers my prayer.
<p></p>
</br>9 He has blocked up my ways with hewn stone. My roadways he has twisted.
<p></p>
</br>10 As a bear lying in wait he is to me, as a lion in places of concealment.
<p></p>
</br>11 My ways he has disarranged, and he makes me lie fallow. He has made me one laid desolate.
<p></p>
</br>12 He has trodden his bow, and he sets me up as the target for the arrow.
<p></p>
</br>13 He has brought into my kidneys the sons of his quiver.
<p></p>
</br>14 I have become an object of laughter to all people against me, the theme of their song all day long.
<p></p>
</br>15 He has given me a sufficiency of bitter things. He has saturated me with wormwood.
<p></p>
</br>16 And with gravel he makes my teeth get broken. He has made me cower in the ashes.
<p></p>
</br>17 You also do a casting off so that there is no peace for my soul. I have lost memory of what good is.
<p></p>
</br>18 And I keep saying: “My excellency has perished, and my expectation from Jehovah.”
<p></p>
</br>19 Remember my affliction and my homeless state, the wormwood and the poisonous plant.
<p></p>
</br>20 Without fail your soul will remember and bow low over me.
<p></p>
</br>21 This is what I shall bring back to my heart. That is why I shall show a waiting attitude.
<p></p>
</br>22 It is the acts of loving-kindness of Jehovah that we have not come to our finish, because his mercies will certainly not come to an end.
<p></p>
</br>23 They are new each morning. Your faithfulness is abundant.
<p></p>
</br>24 “Jehovah is my share,” my soul has said, “that is why I shall show a waiting attitude for him.”
<p></p>
</br>25 Good is Jehovah to the one hoping in him, to the soul that keeps seeking for him.
<p></p>
</br>26 Good it is that one should wait, even silently, for the salvation of Jehovah.
<p></p>
</br>27 Good it is for an able-bodied man that he should carry the yoke during his youth.
<p></p>
</br>28 Let him sit solitary and keep silent, because he has laid [something] upon him.
<p></p>
</br>29 Let him put his mouth in the very dust. Perhaps there exists a hope.
<p></p>
</br>30 Let him give [his] cheek to the very one striking him. Let him have his sufficiency of reproach.
<p></p>
</br>31 For not to time indefinite will Jehovah keep on casting off.
<p></p>
</br>32 For although he has caused grief, he will also certainly show mercy according to the abundance of his loving-kindness.
<p></p>
</br>33 For not out of his own heart has he afflicted or does he grieve the sons of men.
<p></p>
</br>34 For crushing beneath one’s feet all the prisoners of the earth,
<p></p>
</br>35 For turning aside the judgment of an able-bodied man before the face of the Most High,
<p></p>
</br>36 For making a man crooked in his legal case, Jehovah himself has had no countenance.
<p></p>
</br>37 Who, now, has said that something should occur [when] Jehovah himself has not commanded?
<p></p>
</br>38 From the mouth of the Most High bad things and what is good do not go forth.
<p></p>
</br>39 How can a living man indulge in complaints, an able-bodied man on account of his sin?
<p></p>
</br>40 Do let us search out our ways and explore them, and do let us return clear to Jehovah.
<p></p>
</br>41 Let us raise our heart along with [our] palms to God in the heavens:
<p></p>
</br>42 “We ourselves have transgressed, and we have behaved rebelliously. You yourself have not forgiven.
<p></p>
</br>43 You have blocked approach with anger, and you keep pursuing us. You have killed; you have shown no compassion.
<p></p>
</br>44 You have blocked approach to yourself with a cloud mass, that prayer may not pass through.
<p></p>
</br>45 You make us mere offscouring and refuse in the midst of the peoples.”
<p></p>
</br>46 Against us all our enemies have opened their mouth.
<p></p>
</br>47 Dread and the hollow themselves have become ours, desolateness and breakdown.
<p></p>
</br>48 With streams of water my eye keeps running down on account of the breakdown of the daughter of my people.
<p></p>
</br>49 My very eye has been poured forth and will not keep still, so that there are no pauses,
<p></p>
</br>50 Until Jehovah looks down and sees from heaven.
<p></p>
</br>51 My own eye has dealt severely with my soul, because of all the daughters of my city.
<p></p>
</br>52 My enemies have positively hunted for me just as for a bird, for no cause.
<p></p>
</br>53 They have silenced my life in the pit itself, and they kept hurling stones at me.
<p></p>
</br>54 Waters have flowed over my head. I have said: “I shall certainly be cut off!”
<p></p>
</br>55 I have called out your name, O Jehovah, from a pit of the lowest sort.
<p></p>
</br>56 My voice you must hear. Do not hide your ear to my relief, to my cry for help.
<p></p>
</br>57 You have drawn near in the day that I kept calling you. You said: “Do not be afraid.”
<p></p>
</br>58 You have taken up, O Jehovah, the contests of my soul. You have repurchased my life.
<p></p>
</br>59 You have seen, O Jehovah, the wrong done to me. O do conduct the judgment for me.
<p></p>
</br>60 You have seen all their vengeance, all their thoughts against me.
<p></p>
</br>61 You have heard their reproach, O Jehovah, all their thoughts against me,
<p></p>
</br>62 The lips of those rising up against me and their whispering against me all day long.
<p></p>
</br>63 Do look at their very sitting down and their rising up. I am the subject of their song.
<p></p>
</br>64 You will give back to them a treatment, O Jehovah, according to the work of their hands.
<p></p>
</br>65 You will give to them the insolence of heart, your curse to them.
<p></p>
</br>66 You will pursue in anger and annihilate them from under the heavens of Jehovah.
@@libLamentations 
</br>4 :
</br>1 -
</br>22 
<p></p>
</br>1 O how the gold that shines becomes dim, the good gold!
@@citzO how the holy stones are poured out at the head of all the streets!
<p></p>
</br>2 As for the precious sons of Zion, those who were weighed against refined gold,
@@citzO how they have been reckoned as large jars of earthenware, the work of the hands of a potter!
<p></p>
</br>3 Even jackals themselves have presented the udder. They have suckled their cubs.
@@citzThe daughter of my people becomes cruel, like ostriches in the wilderness.
<p></p>
</br>4 The tongue of the suckling has cleaved to its palate because of thirst.
@@citzChildren themselves have asked for bread. There is no one dealing [it] out to them.
<p></p>
</br>5 The very ones that were eating pleasant things have been struck with astonishment in the streets.
@@citzThe very ones that were being reared in scarlet have had to embrace ash heaps.
<p></p>
</br>6 The [punishment for the] error of the daughter of my people also becomes greater than the [punishment for the] sin of Sod´om,
@@citzWhich was overthrown as in a moment, and to which no hands turned [helpfully].
<p></p>
</br>7 Her Naz´i·rites were purer than snow; they were whiter than milk.
@@citzThey were in fact more ruddy than corals; their polish was as the sapphire.
<p></p>
</br>8 Their aspect has become darker than blackness itself. They have not been recognized in the streets.
@@citzTheir skin has shriveled upon their bones. It has become just as dry as a tree.
<p></p>
</br>9 Better have those slain with the sword proved to be than those slain by famine,
@@citzBecause these pine away, pierced through for lack of the produce of the open field.
<p></p>
</br>10 The very hands of compassionate women have boiled their own children.
@@citzThey have become as bread of consolation to one during the breakdown of the daughter of my people.
<p></p>
</br>11 Jehovah has accomplished his rage. He has poured out his burning anger.
@@citzAnd he sets a fire ablaze in Zion, which eats up her foundations.
<p></p>
</br>12 The kings of the earth and all the inhabitants of the productive land had not believed
@@citzThat the adversary and the enemy would come into the gates of Jerusalem.
<p></p>
</br>13 Because of the sins of her prophets, the errors of her priests,
@@citzThere were in the midst of her those pouring out the blood of righteous ones.
<p></p>
</br>14 They have wandered about as blind in the streets. They have become polluted with blood,
@@citzSo that none are able to touch their garments.
<p></p>
</br>15 “Get out of the way! Unclean!” they have called out to them. “Get out of the way! Get out of the way! Do not touch!”
@@citzFor they have gone homeless. They have also wandered about. People have said among the nations: “They will not reside again as aliens.
<p></p>
</br>16 The face of Jehovah has divided them up. He will not look upon them again.
@@citzMen will certainly show no consideration even for the priests. They will certainly show no favor even to the old men.”
<p></p>
</br>17 While we yet are, our eyes keep pining away in vain for assistance to us.
@@citzDuring our looking about we have looked out to a nation that can bring no salvation.
<p></p>
</br>18 They have hunted our steps so that there is no walking in our public squares.
@@citzOur end has drawn near. Our days have come to their full, for our end has come.
<p></p>
</br>19 Swifter than the eagles of the heavens our pursuers have proved to be.
@@citzUpon the mountains they have hotly pursued us. In the wilderness they have lain in wait for us.
<p></p>
</br>20 The very breath of our nostrils, the anointed one of Jehovah, has been captured in their large pit,
@@citzThe one of whom we have said: “In his shade we shall live among the nations.”
<p></p>
</br>21 Exult and rejoice, O daughter of E´dom, dwelling as you do in the land of Uz.
@@citzTo you also the cup will pass along. You will become drunk and show yourself in nakedness.
<p></p>
</br>22 Your error, O daughter of Zion, has come to its finish. He will not carry you off into exile again.
@@citzHe has turned his attention to your error, O daughter of E´dom. He has uncovered your sins.
@@libLamentations 
</br>5 :
</br>1 -
</br>22 
<p></p>
</br>1 Remember, O Jehovah, what has happened to us. Do look and see our reproach.
<p></p>
</br>2 Our own hereditary possession has been turned over to strangers, our houses to foreigners.
<p></p>
</br>3 We have become mere orphans without a father. Our mothers are like widows.
<p></p>
</br>4 For money we have had to drink our own water. For a price our own wood comes in.
<p></p>
</br>5 Close onto our neck we have been pursued. We have grown weary. No rest has been left for us.
<p></p>
</br>6 To Egypt we have given the hand; to As·syr´i·a, in order to get satisfaction with bread.
<p></p>
</br>7 Our forefathers are the ones that have sinned. They are no more. As for us, it is their errors that we have had to bear.
<p></p>
</br>8 Mere servants have ruled over us. There is no one tearing us away from their hand.
<p></p>
</br>9 At the risk of our soul we bring in our bread, because of the sword of the wilderness.
<p></p>
</br>10 Our very skin has grown hot just like a furnace, because of the pangs of hunger.
<p></p>
</br>11 The wives in Zion they have humbled, the virgins in the cities of Judah.
<p></p>
</br>12 Princes themselves have been hanged by just their hand. The faces of even old men have not been honored.
<p></p>
</br>13 Even young men have lifted up a hand mill itself, and under the wood mere boys have stumbled.
<p></p>
</br>14 Old men themselves have ceased even out of the gate, young men from their instrumental music.
<p></p>
</br>15 The exultation of our heart has ceased. Our dancing has been changed into mere mourning.
<p></p>
</br>16 The crown of our head has fallen. Woe, now, to us, because we have sinned!
<p></p>
</br>17 On this account our heart has become ill. On account of these things our eyes have grown dim,
<p></p>
</br>18 On account of Zion’s mountain that is desolated; foxes themselves have walked on it.
<p></p>
</br>19 As for you, O Jehovah, to time indefinite you will sit. Your throne is for generation after generation.
<p></p>
</br>20 Why is it that forever you forget us, that you leave us for the length of days?
<p></p>
</br>21 Bring us back, O Jehovah, to yourself, and we shall readily come back. Bring new days for us as in the long ago.
<p></p>
</br>22 However, you have positively rejected us. You have been indignant toward us very much.